title: CNBC Daily Open: Let’s talk about the Dow
description: On a weekly basis, the S&P advanced 0.79%, the Nasdaq fell 0.57% — but the Dow gained an impressive 2.08%.

title: Here's what the bears are missing, and why there's still money to be made in this bull market
description: If you had to ask me what the bears got most wrong, it's pretty simple: Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell.

title: Spain's right-wing parties could win a parliamentary majority, exit polls show after key election
description: In the absence of a clear majority, the focus is now heavily on who will be the third largest political force emerging from Sunday's election.

title: After 3 days at a Hawaiian resort, couple decides to buy part of it for $1.1 million
description: Joan and Ned Woodward took a vacation to Timbers Kaua'i in Hawaii and, before they left, they decided they would purchase fractional ownership in the resort.

title: Spain votes in a major election that could bring the far right back to power
description: Spain votes in a general election that could see far right party Vox joining the next government in Madrid.

title: Oil markets are still volatile, U.S. energy chief says, calling for further supplies
description: "There's no doubt that there is a volatile environment," U.S. Energy Secretary Jennifer Granholm said.
